What is Root Mean Square Error?

Also called standard error. RMSE is the sum of squared error between predictions and true values divided by the number of predictions and then the square root of that average squared error.  In python: `np.sqrt((np.mean(predictions - true_values) ** 2)`. It is also equivalent to the square root of the dot product of the error vector with itself divided by the number of predictions: `np.sqrt(np.dot(predictions - true_values, predictions - true_values) / len(predictions))`. If you replace the `true_values` in this equation with `0` RMSE is equivalent to the standard deviation. #data-science #statistics #machine-learning
